message.content:
1. The mean pulmonary artery pressure decreased in inoperable patients.
2. The decrease in mean pulmonary artery pressure in inoperable patients was -4.7 mm Hg.
3. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in inoperable patients was -6.9 to -2.6.
4. The p-value for the decrease in inoperable patients was less than 0.0001.
5. The mean pulmonary artery pressure also decreased in persistent/recurrent patients.
6. The decrease in mean pulmonary artery pressure in persistent/recurrent patients was -4.8 mm Hg.
7. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in persistent/recurrent patients was -8.2 to -1.5.
8. The p-value for the decrease in persistent/recurrent patients was 0.0055.
